.TH CUSTODIA-SIGNER 1 "@DATE@" "Custodia @VERSION@" "Custodia Manual"
.SH NAME
custodia-signer \- run the Custodia client certificate signing service
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY custodia-signer
.OP --config FILE
.YS
.SY custodia-signer
.B version
.YS
.SY custodia-signer
.B --version
.YS
.SY custodia-signer
.B help
.YS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B custodia-signer
runs the dedicated Custodia certificate signing service. It signs approved
client mTLS CSRs and keeps CA signing concerns separate from the vault server.
.PP
The signer is optional for purely manual certificate workflows, but it is the
recommended Lite path when using `custodia-admin client sign-csr` for client-generated CSRs. Packaged
installs should use a YAML config file at
.I /etc/custodia/custodia-signer.yaml
with environment variables reserved for overrides.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B version
Print build metadata and exit before loading TLS, CA or signing key material.
.TP
.B --version
Alias for
.BR version .
.TP
.B help, -h, --help
Print usage information and exit before runtime initialization.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --config " FILE"
Load YAML signer configuration before applying environment overrides.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_ADDR
Listen address. Example:
.BR :9444 .
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_TLS_CERT_FILE
TLS server certificate.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_TLS_KEY_FILE
TLS server private key.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_CLIENT_CA_FILE
Client CA bundle used to authenticate admin mTLS clients.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_ADMIN_SUBJECTS
Comma-separated admin certificate subjects authorized to sign CSRs.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_KEY_PROVIDER
Signing key provider. Lite file mode uses
.BR file .
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_CA_CERT_FILE
CA certificate used to issue client certificates.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_CA_KEY_FILE
File-backed CA private key path for Lite deployments.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_CA_KEY_PASSPHRASE_FILE
Optional file-backed CA private key passphrase path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_CRL_FILE
Optional CRL file path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_AUDIT_LOG_FILE
Signer audit JSONL path.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/custodia-signer.yaml
Default packaged signer configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/ca.crt
Default Lite CA certificate.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/ca.key
Default Lite CA private key. Keep readable only by the
.B custodia
service user.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/ca.pass
Optional Lite CA private key passphrase file.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/server.crt
Default signer TLS certificate in packaged Lite examples.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/server.key
Default signer TLS private key in packaged Lite examples.
.TP
.I /var/log/custodia/signer-audit.jsonl
Default signer audit log file.
.SH SYSTEMD
Packaged installs provide
.BR custodia-signer.service .
Typical commands:
.PP
.EX
sudo systemctl enable --now custodia-signer
sudo systemctl status custodia-signer --no-pager
sudo journalctl -u custodia-signer -f
.EE
.SH SECURITY NOTES
.B custodia-signer
may have access to CA signing material, unlike
.BR custodia-server (1).
Keep it isolated, run it as the restricted
.B custodia
user, and prefer HSM/PKCS#11-backed signing for production.
.PP
The signer issues mTLS certificates only; it must not handle application
plaintext, DEKs, or application encryption keys.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run the Lite file-backed signer manually:
.PP
.EX
custodia-signer --config /etc/custodia/custodia-signer.yaml
.EE
.PP
Check build metadata without CA/key initialization:
.PP
.EX
custodia-signer version
.EE
.SH VERSION
Custodia version: @VERSION@
.br
Build commit: @COMMIT@
.br
Build date: @DATE@
.PP
Runtime version is available with:
.PP
.EX
custodia-signer version
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime or signing service failure.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR custodia-admin (1),
.BR custodia-client (1),
.BR custodia-server (1)
